To work with OpenCGA on your Mac
Check if you have Python 3

$ python3 --version
If it displays an error message then install brew to install python 3 :
  $ /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install.sh)"
  $ Password
  Return key
  $ Password

  $ brew install python
  $ python3 --version
  #Should not display an error message anymore

Create an alias to not have to specify python 3
$ alias python=/usr/local/bin/python3
$ python --version
Should display python 3 version (ex : Python 3.9.7)

Install venv for python
$ pip3 install --upgrade virtualenv
Create an environment
$ python3 -m venv venv
Activate the environment
$ source venv/bin/activate
Upgrade pip
$ python3 -m pip install --upgrade pip
Install requirements
$ pip3 install pyopencga==1.4.2.1






